-- Peru Stocks: Atacocha, Buenaventura, Panoro, Volcan
-- B y   A l e x   E m e r y
-- 2012-05-07T21:10:01Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-07/peru-stocks-buenaventura-candente-minsur-southern.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in  Peru  trading. Stock symbols are in parentheses,
and share prices are as of close in  Lima .  The  Lima General Index (IGBVL)  fell 0.8 percent to 21,967.93. The
MSCI All Peru Capped Index slid 0.8 percent to 2,858.55.  Cia. Minera Atacocha SA (ATACOBC1 PE), the Lima-based
silver and zinc mining company, fell 5.4 percent to 52 centimos
after silver declined in New York, said Arlen Lahura, a trader
at brokerage Coril SAB in Lima.  Volcan Cia. Minera SAA (VOLCABC1 PE), Peru’s largest silver
and zinc producer, dropped 1.6 percent to 3.15 soles.  Panoro Minerals Ltd. (PML)  , a Canadian gold and copper
exploration company, slid 2.9 percent to 66 cents after gold
fell in  New York .  Cia. de Minas Buenaventura SAA  (BVN PE), the country’s
biggest precious-metals miner, declined 2 percent to $39.60.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Alex Emery in Lima at 
 aemery1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
David Papadopoulos at 
